# Professional documentation & copy

All READMEs, changelogs, case studies, project descriptions, bios, and other user-facing prose must read like it was written by a senior engineer — not generated by a template.

## Required qualities

- **Specific over vague** — name the product, stack, outcome, or constraint. No filler that could describe any project.
- **Restrained tone** — confident and direct. No hype, no self-congratulation, no marketing fluff.
- **Useful structure** — headings earn their place; lists are scannable; tables only when they clarify.
- **Honest scope** — say what exists today. Do not invent features, metrics, or roadmap items.
- **Consistent voice** — match the existing tone in that repo's README and content/data modules.

## Never use

- Empty openers: "In today's fast-paced world…", "This project aims to…", "Welcome to…"
- Hype words without proof: *revolutionary, cutting-edge, seamless, robust, leverage, empower, delve, landscape, game-changer, next-level*
- Fake depth: "comprehensive overview", "deep dive into", "it's worth noting that", "at its core"
- Engagement bait: "Let's explore…", "Whether you're a beginner or expert…", "Ready to get started?"
- Padding: restating the heading, summarizing what you just said, or adding a closing paragraph that adds nothing
- Emoji in professional docs unless the user explicitly asks for them
- Generic changelogs: "Various bug fixes and improvements", "Updated dependencies" with no context when the change matters

## Write like this

```markdown
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
CssHub is a cutting-edge, seamless solution that empowers developers to leverage
the power of CSS in today's ever-evolving landscape. Whether you're just starting
out or a seasoned pro, this robust tool will revolutionize your workflow!

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
CssHub is a Chrome extension that syncs CSSBattle submissions to your GitHub repo.
OAuth login, content scripts on CSSBattle, automatic commits — no copy-paste.
```

```markdown
<!-- ❌ BAD changelog -->
### Changed
- Improved performance and user experience
- Refactored codebase for better maintainability

<!-- ✅ GOOD changelog -->
### Changed
- Lazy-load project thumbnails on the home page (LCP ~1.2s → ~0.7s on 3G)
- Move portfolio copy into a content module so text edits don't touch layout
```

## Before finishing

1. Cut any sentence that doesn't add information.
2. Replace buzzwords with concrete nouns and verbs.
3. Read aloud once — if it sounds like a landing-page generator, rewrite it.
